  "prompt": "Why did Arnab Goswami left ET now?",
  "response": "Arnab Goswami, a prominent Indian journalist and news anchor, left **Times Now**, which is part of **The Times Group**, in November 2016. He did not leave **ET Now**, which is also part of The Times Group, but rather the parent channel, **Times Now**. His departure was a significant event in the Indian media industry.\n\nThe primary reasons cited for his exit include:\n\n1. **Desire for Independence and Ownership**: Arnab Goswami reportedly wanted greater control and ownership over his work. He sought to establish his own independent news venture where he could shape the editorial direction and content without external constraints.\n\n2. **Creative Differences**: There were speculations of creative differences with the management of The Times Group regarding the editorial direction and priorities of the channel. Goswami was known for his high-decibel, opinion-driven style of journalism, which may have clashed with the management's vision.\n\n3. **Launch of Republic TV**: After leaving Times Now, Goswami founded **Republic TV**, which launched in May 2017. Republic TV reflects his vision of a news channel with a focus on aggressive and opinionated journalism, often targeting current affairs and political debates.\n\nIt's important to clarify that Arnab Goswami's departure was from **Times Now**, not **ET Now**, which is a business-focused channel under the same group. His move was a strategic decision to pursue his entrepreneurial and journalistic ambitions independently.",
